Core Functional Requirements
Focus Timer (Pomodoro Technique)
- Description: A customizable timer to facilitate deep work.
- Game Element: While the timer is active, a "Study Pet"/Hero grows or XP progresses.
- Penalty: If the user leaves the productive-defined site or cancels the timer, the pet/hero loses XP.
- Acceptance Criteria:
   Support 25/50 minute presets and custom durations.
   Background ambient sound options (White noise).

Reward & Progression System
- Description: A dashboard to visualize learning progress.
- Elements: Badges: Earned for milestones (e.g., "7-Day Streak", "10 Hours Focused").
- Shop: Use Gold to buy skins for the timer or virtual items for the pet.
- Acceptance Criteria:
   Visual progress bar for Leveling Up.
   A "Collection Room" for earned badges.

User Stories (For Team Reference)
- I am a student, I want to earn gold for every 25 mins of study so that stay motivated and feel a sense of achievement. 
- I am a developer, I need a local database so that store focus sessions and user currency securely. 
- I am a UI Designer, I need a clear visual style for the "Study Pet" so that ensure the game elements are cute but not distracting. 

Technical Constraints & MVP Scope
- Platform: Mobile/Web (Targeting accessibility).
- MVP (Phase 1): Functional Timer + Basic Task List + Gold Rewards.
- Phase 2: Social Leaderboards + Advanced Pet/Hero Evolution.
